 What's New in Spring Boot 3
Spring Boot 3 introduces several new features and improvements, including:

AOT (Ahead-of-Time) Compilation
Improved startup time and reduced memory footprint through AOT compilation, making it more suitable for serverless environments.
Improved Native Image Support
Native image support has been enhanced, allowing you to compile your Spring Boot application into a native executable using GraalVM, which offers faster startup and lower memory consumption.
Java 17 as the Minimum Requirement
Spring Boot 3 requires Java 17, leveraging the latest language features and performance improvements.